<subSubSection id="BDBBD6735D5D988D13BDD1B6335A118B" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="19263B11E44D8E88ADF918C25EB6AC90" pageNumber="88">Diagnosis</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9F0012DB0BF220A29318744A58776769" pageNumber="88">
Easily distinguished from all other species of the 
<taxonomicName id="BAFA43C24D5B93BBFEBEDCAD3ECCADBF" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="88" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnificus">S. magnificus</taxonomicName>
group by having bright blue lines parallel to rays on all unpaired fins in males (vs. similar lines present only on anterior portion of dorsal fin of 
<taxonomicName id="DF747DA98296B5CDE689B744B8FFE769" LSID-ZBK="urn:lsid:zoobank.org:act:F041EE0E-3680-4BAB-B9FD-17138543CDAB" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName-ZBK="Simpsonichthys adornatus Costa 2000:9" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="88" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="adornatus">S. adornatus</taxonomicName>
or on anal fin of 
<taxonomicName id="47D682FC717549EC4E8D0FA7DBF0F5BA" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="88" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="hellneri">S. hellneri</taxonomicName>
, and absent in the remaining species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4865FDDAC6FBB61DE5BADBF461C0D91E" class="Actinopterygii" family="Rivulidae" genus="Simpsonichthys" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Cyprinodontiformes" pageNumber="88" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="magnificus">S. magnificus</taxonomicName>
group).
